  "prompt": "How did the ring come to Sauron?",
  "response": "The One Ring was originally created by the Dark Lord Sauron himself during the Second Age of Middle-earth. Sauron forged the Ring in the fires of Mount Doom to enhance his power and to control the other Rings of Power given to Elves, Dwarves, and Men. Disguising himself as Annatar, the Lord of Gifts, Sauron deceived the Elven smiths of Eregion and helped them craft the Rings. However, the Elves became aware of his true intentions when he put on the One Ring, and they hid their rings from him.\n\nThe Ring was an integral part of Sauron's strength, binding much of his power to it. He used it to dominate and control, waging war across Middle-earth in an attempt to conquer it. During the War of the Last Alliance, a combined force of Men and Elves fought against Sauron. In the decisive battle at the slopes of Mount Doom, Sauron was defeated when Isildur, son of Elendil, cut the Ring from Sauron's finger, temporarily vanquishing him.\n\nThough Sauron was defeated and his physical form destroyed, his essence persisted as long as the Ring existed. The Ring subsequently was lost for many centuries until it was found by Gollum and then passed to Bilbo Baggins and eventually to Frodo Baggins, setting off the events of \"The Lord of the Rings.\" Throughout this time, Sauron continued to seek his precious Ring to regain his full power and dominion over Middle-earth.",
